        "pricing"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-ship-fast-charge-early",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best tech stack for an indie project is the one you can ship with today. Not the one you'll learn eventually.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "indie-hacker",
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "tech-stack",
        "shipping"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-tech-stack",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Ship it, then fix it. Nobody sees your bugs until you've told them where to look.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "indie-hacker",
        "shipping"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "shipping",
        "bugs"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-ship-it-then-fix",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time to add a 'What's New' page is after you've shipped something worth announcing. Not before.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "saas"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "changelog",
        "shipping"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-time-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If you can't test it, you can't ship it. If you can't ship it, you can't charge for it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "testing",
        "shipping"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-you-cant-test",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Every line of code is a liability. Every feature is a bet. Every deploy is a risk. Ship accordingly.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "risk",
        "shipping"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-every-line-of-code",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Indie hackers who ship weekly grow faster than indie hackers who ship quarterly. Ship more, learn faster.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "indie-hacker"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "shipping",
        "velocity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-indie-hackers-who-ship",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your stack doesn't matter. Your ship rate does. Ship weekly or don't ship at all.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "indie-hacker"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "shipping",
        "tech-stack"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-stack-doesnt-matter",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Done is better than perfect. Shipped is better than done. Revenue is better than shipped.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "shipping",
        "priorities"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-done-is-better-than",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Indie hackers who ship weekly have 10x the chances of finding product-market fit than those who ship quarterly.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "indie-hacker"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "shipping",
        "velocity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-indie-hackers-who-ship",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best SaaS teams ship weekly. Not because speed is a virtue, but because momentum compounds.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "saas"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "shipping",
        "momentum"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
